WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:25.333 --> 00:01:27.458
Let me go. Tony. for Pete's sake.

3
00:01:27.542 --> 00:01:29.792
Mr. Pete. you decide.

4
00:01:29.875 --> 00:01:30.792
How to handle her?

5
00:01:30.875 --> 00:01:33.167
Only Dad gets

6
00:01:33.250 --> 00:01:34.667
to decide her future!

7
00:01:57.917 --> 00:01:58.958
Sit.

8
00:02:02.208 --> 00:02:04.792
You gave your word. Jaggu.

9
00:02:05.917 --> 00:02:07.917
But three years just flew by.

10
00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:10.917
and you still couldn't find
a single match for my grandson!

11
00:02:14.208 --> 00:02:17.167
Excuse me? I showed you
three hundred girls in three years.

12
00:02:18.042 --> 00:02:21.167
You rejected them
over family details or even their diet!

13
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:24.417
And the few you actually liked?

14
00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:26.583
They vanished into thin air!

15
00:02:26.958 --> 00:02:28.583
These modern girls

16
00:02:28.667 --> 00:02:31.167
don't want to live in a extended family.

17
00:02:31.250 --> 00:02:33.333
We're not looking
for that kind of girl.

18
00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:39.167
Jaggu. give it one more shot.

19
00:02:40.583 --> 00:02:42.667
There has to be someone.

20
00:02:43.375 --> 00:02:44.250
Speak up.

21
00:02:44.333 --> 00:02:45.917
There is.

22
00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:47.958
She ticks every box.

23
00:02:48.042 --> 00:02:50.125
Beautiful. educated.

24
00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:52.833
and totally okay
with a big extended family.

25
00:02:53.208 --> 00:02:54.917
But... there's a tiny catch.

26
00:02:55.333 --> 00:02:56.708
What catch?

27
00:02:57.708 --> 00:02:59.917
First. take a look at her picture.

28
00:03:01.167 --> 00:03:02.167
Here.

29
00:03:06.042 --> 00:03:07.250
Check this. Tony.

30
00:03:09.500 --> 00:03:11.875
She's Kanika Ahuja.
From Greater Kailash.

31
00:03:12.750 --> 00:03:14.208
Do you know her?

32
00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:16.708
Yeah. we were in the same college.

33
00:03:16.792 --> 00:03:17.833
Perfect!

34
00:03:17.917 --> 00:03:18.917
Then it's settled.

35
00:03:18.958 --> 00:03:21.083
They already know each other!

36
00:03:21.167 --> 00:03:22.458
I know her. Mom.

37
00:03:22.542 --> 00:03:23.750
She doesn't know me.

38
00:03:23.833 --> 00:03:25.250
She was a medical student.

39
00:03:25.333 --> 00:03:26.750
And you?

40
00:03:26.833 --> 00:03:28.125
I was an Arts student.

41
00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:30.292
Ah. a classic one-sided love story.

42
00:03:38.583 --> 00:03:40.625
So what's the problem now?

43
00:03:40.708 --> 00:03:43.208
The "problem" is

44
00:03:43.667 --> 00:03:48.042
she first wants
to know the groom's family

45
00:03:48.125 --> 00:03:49.375
and marry after two years.

46
00:03:49.458 --> 00:03:50.583
Two years?!

47
00:03:50.667 --> 00:03:51.958
Say yes to her terms.

48
00:03:52.042 --> 00:03:54.250
and we'll get them engaged right away.

49
00:03:54.333 --> 00:03:56.500
But he's already three years late.

50
00:03:56.583 --> 00:03:57.583
Two more years...

51
00:03:58.292 --> 00:03:59.292
Relax. Grandpa.

52
00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:02.167
Three years flew by.
Two more won't hurt.

53
00:04:10.292 --> 00:04:12.417
If Tony's made up his mind.

54
00:04:12.792 --> 00:04:14.192
let's go ahead with the engagement.

55
00:04:26.375 --> 00:04:28.958
<i>♪ A glimpse of her ♪</i>

56
00:04:29.042 --> 00:04:34.625
<i>♪ Just a glimpse of her ♪</i>

57
00:04:34.708 --> 00:04:37.500
<i>♪ Just one glimpse ♪</i>

58
00:04:37.583 --> 00:04:43.125
<i>♪ Feels like heaven itself ♪</i>

59
00:04:43.208 --> 00:04:47.583
<i>♪ Wherever she steps</i> ♪

60
00:04:47.667 --> 00:04:52.083
<i>♪ It's like roses bloom in her path ♪</i>

61
00:04:53.083 --> 00:04:58.750
<i>♪ Yes. roses bloom. </i>my love ♪

62
00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:03.500
<i>♪ wherever she steps ♪</i>

63
00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:22.125
<i>♪ Your wish is my command ♪</i>

64
00:05:22.208 --> 00:05:27.625
<i>♪ If you ever look away
I swear I'd die ♪</i>

65
00:05:27.708 --> 00:05:33.250
<i>♪ I'd break my fast seeing your face ♪</i>

66
00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:38.833
<i>♪ You're on my mind all day long ♪</i>

67
00:05:38.917 --> 00:05:44.292
<i>♪ Nothing else feels special
When you're around ♪</i>

68
00:05:44.375 --> 00:05:48.917
<i>♪ Even the city looks more beautiful ♪</i>

69
00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:54.333
<i>♪ Roses bloom. my love</i> ♪

70
00:05:54.417 --> 00:05:59.042
<i>♪ Wherever she steps ♪</i>

71
00:05:59.958 --> 00:06:05.667
<i>♪ Roses bloom. my love</i> ♪

72
00:06:05.792 --> 00:06:10.375
<i>♪ Wherever she steps ♪</i>

73
00:06:11.083 --> 00:06:17.708
<i>♪ Yes. roses bloom wherever she steps ♪</i>

74
00:06:21.208 --> 00:06:23.000
Grandpa's coming too. Let's go!

75
00:06:23.083 --> 00:06:25.250
Why don't you want to go?
It's getting late.

76
00:06:25.333 --> 00:06:26.333
Tony.

77
00:06:28.208 --> 00:06:30.292
Hurry up. dear. It's getting late.

78
00:06:51.583 --> 00:06:53.083
Grandma is getting married!

79
00:06:53.167 --> 00:06:54.875
Grandma is getting married!

80
00:06:54.958 --> 00:06:56.375
Grandma is getting married!

81
00:06:58.833 --> 00:07:00.292
Grandma is getting married!

82
00:07:00.375 --> 00:07:01.875
Grandma is getting married!

83
00:07:06.208 --> 00:07:07.792
Grandma is getting married!

84
00:07:31.792 --> 00:07:33.792
Mr. Ahuja's mother must
be well past seventy.

85
00:07:33.875 --> 00:07:36.708
The granddaughter's getting engaged
and Grandma's tying the knot!

86
00:07:36.792 --> 00:07:38.750
What has the world come to?
Grandma's wedding.

87
00:07:38.833 --> 00:07:40.250
She also posted it on social media.

88
00:07:40.333 --> 00:07:42.417
No shame at all.

89
00:07:42.792 --> 00:07:43.851
Mom's phone is unreachable.

90
00:07:43.875 --> 00:07:45.125
Naag isn't picking up. Idiot.

91
00:07:45.208 --> 00:07:46.417
Call Sunaina.

92
00:07:47.958 --> 00:07:49.333
Sunaina is his younger sister.

93
00:07:50.208 --> 00:07:51.458
I don't have Sunaina's number.

94
00:07:51.667 --> 00:07:53.792
You don't have your sister's number?

95
00:07:53.875 --> 00:07:55.115
What kind of a brother are you!

96
00:07:56.042 --> 00:07:57.875
This must be a misunderstanding.

97
00:07:57.958 --> 00:08:01.417
You should clear up this misunderstanding.

98
00:08:02.125 --> 00:08:03.708
Keep it clear.

99
00:08:03.792 --> 00:08:05.250
Stay in cheer.

100
00:08:05.333 --> 00:08:07.417
If your mother gets married.

101
00:08:07.792 --> 00:08:09.875
then my grandson Tony

102
00:08:10.375 --> 00:08:13.000
will not marry your daughter.

103
00:08:21.375 --> 00:08:23.000
See you. God bless.

104
00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:27.000
Come on.

105
00:08:53.833 --> 00:08:56.792
He's a weird guy. this Naagendra.
Never picks up his phone.

106
00:08:56.875 --> 00:08:57.875
Here.

107
00:08:58.792 --> 00:09:00.083
Who else can I call in Shimla?

108
00:09:02.833 --> 00:09:04.101
Mom's phone is still turned off.

109
00:09:04.125 --> 00:09:05.500
She is unbelievable.

110
00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:08.520
Where did you go
during the engagement?

111
00:09:08.625 --> 00:09:10.333
I just went to the bathroom. Dad.

112
00:09:10.417 --> 00:09:12.208
And you took the iPad along?

113
00:09:12.292 --> 00:09:14.375
Who does that?

114
00:09:15.875 --> 00:09:17.042
That's the problem with you.

115
00:09:17.792 --> 00:09:19.875
You always target someone else
for others' mistakes.

116
00:09:20.875 --> 00:09:22.667
Our daughter's engagement was called off

117
00:09:22.750 --> 00:09:24.500
because of your mom's decision.

118
00:09:25.042 --> 00:09:27.792
And this will also affect Bittu's future.

119
00:09:27.875 --> 00:09:28.917
Mom. relax.

120
00:09:29.208 --> 00:09:30.792
We'll find someone else.

121
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:32.601
Someone who's okay with
Grandma getting married.

122
00:09:32.625 --> 00:09:33.625
Keep quiet.

123
00:09:34.500 --> 00:09:35.667
Did anyone ask you?

124
00:09:35.750 --> 00:09:37.583
At least she has opinions.

125
00:09:37.667 --> 00:09:38.787
You're not thinking clearly.

126
00:09:38.833 --> 00:09:40.125
Can you stop taking digs at me?

127
00:09:40.917 --> 00:09:42.542
My mom's getting married. not me!

128
00:09:42.625 --> 00:09:44.708
Honestly. it should've been you instead.

129
00:09:44.792 --> 00:09:45.875
I would be free by now.

130
00:09:45.958 --> 00:09:47.375
Don't you...

131
00:09:48.042 --> 00:09:49.042
Naag is calling.

132
00:09:49.542 --> 00:09:51.583
Naag... which phone do you have?

133
00:09:51.667 --> 00:09:55.375
It's an iPhone 16 Pro Max
Titanium Grey 1 TB.

134
00:09:55.458 --> 00:09:56.833
<i>It's useless. You never pick up.</i>

135
00:09:56.917 --> 00:09:59.708
If I'm dying on the streets.
you still won't pick up.

136
00:09:59.792 --> 00:10:01.708
Don't be so negative. Brother.

137
00:10:01.792 --> 00:10:02.958
A guy could be busy.

138
00:10:03.042 --> 00:10:05.042
Recently finished the township project.

139
00:10:05.125 --> 00:10:07.625
<i>and flew to Uttarakhand
to get Mother Goddess's blessing.</i>

140
00:10:07.708 --> 00:10:08.708
So. what happened?

141
00:10:08.958 --> 00:10:11.042
Look at mom's Facelook status.

142
00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:25.042
What happened. Naag?

143
00:10:45.333 --> 00:10:46.917
Hello. sir.

144
00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:47.875
- Greetings.
- God bless.

145
00:10:47.958 --> 00:10:49.625
- Tony?
- Hello.

146
00:10:49.708 --> 00:10:50.750
Bless you. son.

147
00:10:50.958 --> 00:10:52.458
Tony. what brings you here?

148
00:10:52.542 --> 00:10:54.833
I came here to apologize

149
00:10:54.917 --> 00:10:56.018
for what grandpa said yesterday...

150
00:10:56.042 --> 00:10:58.333
What your grandpa said was right. Tony.

151
00:10:59.208 --> 00:11:00.888
If Kannu's grandma goes through with this.

152
00:11:00.917 --> 00:11:04.042
we won't be able to
show our faces in public!

153
00:11:05.625 --> 00:11:07.208
Have you spoken to anyone?

154
00:11:07.292 --> 00:11:09.750
We can't reach her.
so we're going to Shimla to see her.

155
00:11:10.333 --> 00:11:12.500
I see. Okay. fine.

156
00:11:13.125 --> 00:11:13.958
How are you guys traveling?

157
00:11:14.042 --> 00:11:15.750
We'll take a train to Chandigarh.

158
00:11:15.833 --> 00:11:17.074
My younger brother lives there.

159
00:11:17.125 --> 00:11:18.708
Then we'll travel by road to Shimla.

160
00:11:18.792 --> 00:11:20.208
Did you buy tickets?

161
00:11:20.292 --> 00:11:21.492
We'll buy them at the station.

162
00:11:21.542 --> 00:11:22.917
I'll drop you off at the station.

163
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.250
Don't trouble yourself.

164
00:11:24.333 --> 00:11:26.083
We're close. It's no trouble.

165
00:11:26.167 --> 00:11:29.125
- Come on. Come on. sir. Just come.
- Doesn't feel right.

166
00:11:44.542 --> 00:11:45.750
Ma'am. Sir.

167
00:11:45.833 --> 00:11:46.833
You are good to go.

168
00:11:46.917 --> 00:11:48.708
The train departs from Platform 4.

169
00:11:48.792 --> 00:11:49.958
I'll park the car.

170
00:11:50.042 --> 00:11:53.000
And don't buy any tickets.
I already bought them online.

171
00:11:53.083 --> 00:11:54.292
Oh...

172
00:11:54.375 --> 00:11:55.375
Come on.

173
00:12:02.708 --> 00:12:03.750
Come on.

174
00:12:09.458 --> 00:12:10.750
Oh. God.

175
00:12:11.500 --> 00:12:14.667
- What happened?
- I mistakenly booked an extra ticket.

176
00:12:14.750 --> 00:12:15.833
Not to worry.

177
00:12:15.917 --> 00:12:17.542
It's a crime to travel without a ticket.

178
00:12:17.625 --> 00:12:19.875
It's okay if you buy a ticket
and don't travel.

179
00:12:19.958 --> 00:12:21.375
The ticket will go to waste.

180
00:12:21.458 --> 00:12:23.792
Why will it go to waste?
I'll go with you to Chandigarh.

181
00:12:25.125 --> 00:12:26.125
My friend lives there.

182
00:12:26.208 --> 00:12:28.458
I will surprise him.
He will be really happy.

183
00:12:28.542 --> 00:12:30.083
Thanks for coming with us. Tony.

184
00:12:30.167 --> 00:12:32.458
At least we'll have some fun company.

185
00:12:36.958 --> 00:12:38.083
Want a candy. Bittu?

186
00:12:38.167 --> 00:12:40.250
Yes! Give me one!

187
00:12:41.292 --> 00:12:43.532
Let's buy one in Chandigarh.
We'll get better ones there.

188
00:12:44.750 --> 00:12:47.750
The internet has spoiled
everyone's habits. sir.

189
00:12:47.833 --> 00:12:49.083
Yeah...

190
00:12:49.167 --> 00:12:51.917
Our grandpa never bought us iPads.

191
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.708
They didn't exist back then.

192
00:12:53.792 --> 00:12:55.875
True.

193
00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:07.833
Kannu.

194
00:13:09.167 --> 00:13:10.167
Tony.

195
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:12.184
Where does your friend live in Chandigarh?

196
00:13:12.208 --> 00:13:13.208
Monty?

197
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.333
- He lives in a house.
- Oh...

198
00:13:15.417 --> 00:13:17.958
- Doesn't he go to his sweet shop?
- A sweet shop?

199
00:13:18.042 --> 00:13:19.500
A doctor's friend is a doctor.

200
00:13:19.583 --> 00:13:20.917
A teacher's friend is a teacher.

201
00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:22.518
So a sweet maker's friend must
also be a sweet maker. right?

202
00:13:22.542 --> 00:13:24.458
We are not sweet makers.

203
00:13:24.542 --> 00:13:25.708
Kalra Sweets is a brand.

204
00:13:25.792 --> 00:13:27.292
We have 17 outlets in Delhi.

205
00:13:27.375 --> 00:13:29.583
We just opened a new one in Shahdara.

206
00:13:29.667 --> 00:13:31.792
And before our wedding.
we'll launch one in Dubai too.

207
00:13:31.875 --> 00:13:34.208
But if my grandma
gets married. that plan is off.

208
00:13:36.042 --> 00:13:38.333
So tell me. what are your intentions?

209
00:13:40.542 --> 00:13:41.542
Hey. easy.

210
00:13:42.917 --> 00:13:45.000
My intentions are pure. Always have been.

211
00:13:46.208 --> 00:13:48.833
What do you think about
your grandma's marriage?

212
00:13:52.042 --> 00:13:54.792
Tony. if my grandma
wants to get married.

213
00:13:55.125 --> 00:13:57.208
no grandpa in the world can stop her.

214
00:14:25.042 --> 00:14:26.500
Bittu!

215
00:14:26.958 --> 00:14:28.375
Uncle! Aunt!

216
00:14:28.458 --> 00:14:30.083
Hello.

217
00:14:30.167 --> 00:14:32.042
- Greetings. Brother!
- Greetings.

218
00:14:32.125 --> 00:14:33.042
Greetings. Sister-in-law!

219
00:14:33.125 --> 00:14:35.333
- Kannu!
- How are you?

220
00:14:36.875 --> 00:14:38.958
- Greetings. Brother-in-law.
- Bless you.

221
00:14:39.042 --> 00:14:40.042
Are those for offering?

222
00:14:40.083 --> 00:14:41.083
Fenugreek <i>Laddu</i>.

223
00:14:41.125 --> 00:14:42.208
Good for blood pressure.

224
00:14:42.292 --> 00:14:43.643
I've already given
him three since morning.

225
00:14:43.667 --> 00:14:44.893
Sister-in-law. you also have one.

226
00:14:44.917 --> 00:14:47.000
- Thank you.
- Leave it. Baby.

227
00:14:48.292 --> 00:14:49.667
Greetings!

228
00:14:49.750 --> 00:14:51.833
- Bittu. let's load the luggage.
- Yes.

229
00:14:52.208 --> 00:14:53.083
Bobby!

230
00:14:53.167 --> 00:14:54.208
- Who is this?
- Aunt!

231
00:14:54.292 --> 00:14:55.917
Yes. I'll tell you later.

232
00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:58.292
Where's Bobby?

233
00:14:58.375 --> 00:15:00.333
Hey. Uncle! Aunt!

234
00:15:00.417 --> 00:15:01.292
Hello. son.

235
00:15:01.375 --> 00:15:03.458
- Bobby! What's up?
- What's up!

236
00:15:03.875 --> 00:15:06.125
Enough with that.
Wake up and drive the car.

237
00:15:06.208 --> 00:15:07.875
You drive. He's tired.

238
00:15:07.958 --> 00:15:10.042
I drove all night. and he's tired?

239
00:15:10.125 --> 00:15:12.542
People do get tired during travel.

240
00:15:12.625 --> 00:15:14.708
Go lie down in the backseat. son.

241
00:15:15.542 --> 00:15:17.417
Then who's driving the Volvo. Brother?

242
00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:19.000
Don't worry. I'll drive.

243
00:15:20.333 --> 00:15:21.893
You? How will you drive?
Doesn't your friend live here...

244
00:15:21.917 --> 00:15:23.042
Friends can wait.

245
00:15:23.125 --> 00:15:25.208
First. we go to Shimla
and sort out the family issue.

246
00:15:25.667 --> 00:15:26.833
Everything else can follow.

247
00:15:26.917 --> 00:15:28.750
Family comes first. right. sir?

248
00:15:28.833 --> 00:15:30.917
Give me the keys. Come on.

249
00:15:32.833 --> 00:15:34.000
Family?

250
00:15:34.708 --> 00:15:35.833
Why so friendly?

251
00:15:38.208 --> 00:15:41.083
Kannu got engaged.
and we weren't even invited?

252
00:15:41.167 --> 00:15:43.833
It all happened just two days ago.

253
00:15:43.917 --> 00:15:45.583
We didn't get time make calls.

254
00:15:45.667 --> 00:15:47.125
You could've at least messaged.

255
00:15:47.208 --> 00:15:49.875
Why complain about something
that didn't even happen. Aunt?

256
00:15:50.208 --> 00:15:51.958
The engagement has been called off.

257
00:15:52.042 --> 00:15:54.250
But a bond has been formed. Kannu.

258
00:15:54.333 --> 00:15:55.894
The wedding is right around the corner.

259
00:15:56.417 --> 00:15:59.250
And the Kalras are
definitely inviting you too. sir.

260
00:15:59.333 --> 00:16:01.000
Which Kalra family?

261
00:16:01.083 --> 00:16:03.333
Me. Myself. Tony Kalra.

262
00:16:03.667 --> 00:16:05.708
And soon. Kannu will be part of it too.

263
00:16:05.792 --> 00:16:06.958
As Kannu Kalra.

264
00:16:07.042 --> 00:16:10.458
But if grandma gets married
then she stays Kannu Ahuja.

265
00:16:11.375 --> 00:16:12.417
Exactly.

266
00:16:12.500 --> 00:16:14.583
Son. if Mom gets married.

267
00:16:15.750 --> 00:16:17.833
none of us will be Ahujas anymore.

268
00:16:18.958 --> 00:16:21.083
Everyone's last name will change.

269
00:17:36.708 --> 00:17:37.708
Jeevan?

270
00:17:39.042 --> 00:17:40.083
Naag?

271
00:17:41.042 --> 00:17:42.042
Daughter-in-law?

272
00:17:42.500 --> 00:17:43.542
Grandma!

273
00:17:43.625 --> 00:17:44.750
Suddenly?

274
00:17:46.708 --> 00:17:48.000
Kannu!

275
00:17:48.333 --> 00:17:49.458
Come in!

276
00:17:49.542 --> 00:17:50.958
Why is your phone turned off. Mom?

277
00:17:51.042 --> 00:17:52.268
We've been trying since yesterday.

278
00:17:52.292 --> 00:17:54.125
It wasn't charged.

279
00:17:54.208 --> 00:17:56.250
There was no electricity
in Shimla for two days.

280
00:17:56.333 --> 00:17:59.125
It's been waiting for you all.
just like me.

281
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.000
Should I make tea or some snacks first?

282
00:18:02.083 --> 00:18:03.208
- Nothing for me.
- Grandma!

283
00:18:03.292 --> 00:18:04.542
Something like...

284
00:18:04.625 --> 00:18:05.542
<i>Bhurji Paratha</i>?

285
00:18:05.625 --> 00:18:06.768
- Nothing. thanks.
- I want the <i>Siddu </i>you make.

286
00:18:06.792 --> 00:18:07.667
Siddu.

287
00:18:07.750 --> 00:18:09.750
- Or <i>Paneer Makhani</i>?
- Paneer Makhani. it is.

288
00:18:09.833 --> 00:18:11.708
My. how you've grown. child.

289
00:18:11.792 --> 00:18:13.417
- Greetings.
- Bless you.

290
00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:14.792
- Keep it over there.
- Okay.

291
00:18:14.875 --> 00:18:17.250
Grandma. were you
playing cricket at night?

292
00:18:17.333 --> 00:18:19.125
Who plays cricket alone?

293
00:18:19.208 --> 00:18:21.833
Now that you're here.
we'll play together.

294
00:18:21.917 --> 00:18:23.333
Done!

295
00:18:23.417 --> 00:18:24.958
Grandma. don't you have Wi-Fi?

296
00:18:25.042 --> 00:18:27.000
I'll get one if you all stay longer.

297
00:18:27.083 --> 00:18:29.333
By the way. how long are you staying?

298
00:18:29.417 --> 00:18:31.125
Till the wedding. Grandma.

299
00:18:31.208 --> 00:18:32.708
I didn't recognize you.

300
00:18:32.792 --> 00:18:34.333
- I...
- He's Tony Kalra. Mom.

301
00:18:34.417 --> 00:18:36.375
Kannu's fiancé.

302
00:18:36.458 --> 00:18:38.125
- Grandson-in-law is here.
- Hello.

303
00:18:38.208 --> 00:18:39.542
You should've told me earlier.

304
00:18:39.625 --> 00:18:41.417
I would've made proper arrangements.

305
00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:43.375
I'll be back in a minute.

306
00:18:43.458 --> 00:18:45.139
"Grandson-in-law". More like a forced one.

307
00:18:45.583 --> 00:18:47.833
Mom. where should I keep this setup?

308
00:18:47.917 --> 00:18:49.458
In Dad's room upstairs.

309
00:18:49.542 --> 00:18:50.833
Why are you standing quietly?

310
00:18:50.917 --> 00:18:52.125
Ask your mom.

311
00:18:52.208 --> 00:18:53.208
How can I...

312
00:18:54.083 --> 00:18:55.125
Naag.

313
00:18:55.208 --> 00:18:56.125
you ask.

314
00:18:56.208 --> 00:18:57.375
She's your mom.

315
00:18:57.458 --> 00:18:58.625
And yours too.

316
00:18:58.708 --> 00:18:59.708
You're the eldest.

317
00:18:59.750 --> 00:19:01.042
Is it my fault I'm older?

318
00:19:01.125 --> 00:19:03.417
You've been saying that since childhood!

319
00:19:03.500 --> 00:19:04.833
Feels strange

320
00:19:04.917 --> 00:19:07.125
asking my own mom about her marriage.

321
00:19:08.583 --> 00:19:10.208
Feels awkward.

322
00:19:10.292 --> 00:19:13.667
Mother-in-law announced it
on Facelook for the whole world...

323
00:19:13.750 --> 00:19:16.458
And you feel awkward asking?

324
00:19:16.542 --> 00:19:18.684
Wait till you have to perform
your mom's wedding rituals.

325
00:19:18.708 --> 00:19:21.208
Then you'll know what awkward means.

326
00:19:21.708 --> 00:19:22.833
Honestly. sir.

327
00:19:22.917 --> 00:19:25.000
there is no wedding vibe here.

328
00:19:25.083 --> 00:19:26.500
Don't judge by appearances. Tony.

329
00:19:26.583 --> 00:19:30.208
We thought you'd just drop us
at the station and leave...

330
00:19:30.625 --> 00:19:32.417
But you came all the way to Shimla.

331
00:19:32.500 --> 00:19:34.583
Destiny. Kannu.

332
00:19:39.875 --> 00:19:41.000
Bless you. son.

333
00:19:41.917 --> 00:19:44.250
May you always stay happy.

334
00:19:45.125 --> 00:19:46.417
No need for this. ma'am.

335
00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:48.083
It's a blessing. Keep it.

336
00:19:48.167 --> 00:19:49.500
Thank you. ma'am.

337
00:19:49.583 --> 00:19:53.083
I was shocked to see all of you together.

338
00:19:53.167 --> 00:19:54.667
Mom

339
00:19:54.750 --> 00:19:56.833
didn't you even... think once...

340
00:19:56.917 --> 00:19:57.917
Think what?

341
00:19:57.958 --> 00:19:59.750
Brother means...

342
00:19:59.833 --> 00:20:01.917
You...

343
00:20:02.625 --> 00:20:03.917
What do you want to ask?

344
00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.458
Grandma. are you getting married?

345
00:20:07.667 --> 00:20:08.958
We'll talk in the morning.

346
00:20:09.042 --> 00:20:10.833
You've all had a long journey.

347
00:20:10.917 --> 00:20:11.958
Get some rest.

348
00:20:12.042 --> 00:20:14.167
No one's sleeping tonight. ma'am.

349
00:20:14.250 --> 00:20:16.333
They gathered a lot
of courage to ask you.

350
00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:18.250
So... are you really getting married?

351
00:20:20.208 --> 00:20:21.292
Yes.

352
00:20:21.375 --> 00:20:24.375
- What!
- Yes. I am getting married.

353
00:20:24.458 --> 00:20:26.167
- Mom...
- Mom...

354
00:20:26.250 --> 00:20:27.643
We'll continue this in the morning.

355
00:20:27.667 --> 00:20:29.333
I'm very sleepy.

356
00:20:29.417 --> 00:20:31.625
You all get some rest. Goodnight.

357
00:20:31.708 --> 00:20:33.458
- Mother-in-law...
- Mom...

358
00:20:33.542 --> 00:20:35.142
- We'll talk tomorrow.
- Mother-in-law...

359
00:20:35.167 --> 00:20:36.292
Mom...

360
00:20:52.292 --> 00:20:53.792
Congratulations. Grandma.

361
00:20:54.167 --> 00:20:55.667
But you could've told me.

362
00:20:55.750 --> 00:20:57.667
I've been in touch with you regularly.

363
00:20:57.750 --> 00:21:01.583
Liking posts and dropping comments
on Facelook is not "keeping in touch".

364
00:21:01.667 --> 00:21:03.792
Even you didn't tell me
about your engagement.

365
00:21:04.292 --> 00:21:05.500
I didn't get engaged. Grandma.

366
00:21:05.583 --> 00:21:07.958
It was called off right
after your wedding news.

367
00:21:08.042 --> 00:21:09.458
What do you mean?

368
00:21:09.542 --> 00:21:11.042
Don't worry. Grandma.

369
00:21:11.125 --> 00:21:13.208
I never wanted to get married anyway.

370
00:21:13.708 --> 00:21:17.083
I said yes
because Mom and Dad insisted.

371
00:21:17.167 --> 00:21:19.750
- I even added the two-year condition.
- Why?

372
00:21:19.833 --> 00:21:22.708
I don't want to live in India.
There's nothing here for me.

373
00:21:22.792 --> 00:21:24.958
No job opportunities. no freedom

374
00:21:25.125 --> 00:21:26.375
honestly. nothing.

375
00:21:27.875 --> 00:21:31.042
Grandma. I want to settle
in New Zealand. Permanently.

376
00:21:31.417 --> 00:21:34.167
I've already applied
for my dream job there.

377
00:21:34.250 --> 00:21:35.917
And what about Tony?

378
00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:37.917
- What about him?
- He'll marry someone else.

379
00:21:38.000 --> 00:21:40.083
But I'm so happy for you.

380
00:22:59.125 --> 00:23:01.875
By the way. what exactly
did you write on Facelook?

381
00:23:01.958 --> 00:23:04.167
Ratna's daughter was getting married.

382
00:23:04.500 --> 00:23:05.708
so I posted...

383
00:23:05.958 --> 00:23:08.667
"Himani getting married. feeling happy."

384
00:23:09.042 --> 00:23:10.667
Auto-correct turned it into...

385
00:23:10.750 --> 00:23:13.792
"Hi. I am getting married.
feeling happy."

386
00:23:14.958 --> 00:23:16.917
Fine. they misunderstood.

387
00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:18.417
But why didn't you correct it?

388
00:23:20.333 --> 00:23:22.792
What would've happened
if you had told them the truth?

389
00:23:22.875 --> 00:23:25.000
They would've left immediately.

390
00:23:25.083 --> 00:23:28.250
Everything else in their lives
matters more than their mother.

391
00:23:28.333 --> 00:23:31.292
They all showed up together
after seven years

392
00:23:31.375 --> 00:23:34.833
and didn't even tell Vimla
about Kannu's engagement.

393
00:23:34.917 --> 00:23:38.625
So when they asked.
I just said I was getting married.

394
00:23:39.250 --> 00:23:41.875
At least this way.
they'll stay with me for a few days.

395
00:23:42.208 --> 00:23:43.750
But what's the point?

396
00:23:43.833 --> 00:23:46.750
Even if they stay.
they'll look at you with resentment.

397
00:23:47.333 --> 00:23:49.042
Let them.

398
00:23:49.667 --> 00:23:51.292
At least they'll be in front of my eyes.

399
00:23:52.042 --> 00:23:53.500
That's enough for me.

400
00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:55.583
Even if we argue

401
00:23:55.667 --> 00:23:58.208
a mother's life is about being
around her children.

402
00:23:59.167 --> 00:24:00.667
Hi. beautiful ladies.

403
00:24:11.667 --> 00:24:13.875
I hope that flippant trips and falls.

404
00:24:22.542 --> 00:24:23.417
Tony...

405
00:24:23.500 --> 00:24:25.125
I feel terrible.

406
00:24:25.208 --> 00:24:27.333
Your marriage got canceled
because of his mother.

407
00:24:27.417 --> 00:24:30.333
Please apologize to your grandpa
on our behalf.

408
00:24:30.958 --> 00:24:32.333
Enough with the apologies. Tony.

409
00:24:32.417 --> 00:24:33.625
Give us a plan.

410
00:24:37.333 --> 00:24:39.250
Try emotional blackmailing.

411
00:24:39.792 --> 00:24:41.083
She's a mother. she'll melt.

412
00:24:41.792 --> 00:24:43.250
Remind her of old memories.

413
00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:45.583
Use your father as leverage.

414
00:24:45.667 --> 00:24:46.917
Use who as leverage. Tony?

415
00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:49.083
Breakfast. ma'am.
Serve her breakfast.

416
00:24:49.417 --> 00:24:51.542
Did you all sleep well last night?

417
00:24:51.625 --> 00:24:52.625
Yes. Mom.

418
00:24:53.542 --> 00:24:55.542
- No. Mom...
- Why?

419
00:24:55.625 --> 00:24:57.500
Dad visited me in my dream.

420
00:24:57.583 --> 00:24:58.583
Did he?

421
00:24:58.667 --> 00:25:01.333
He seemed upset about your remarriage.

422
00:25:01.417 --> 00:25:02.667
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

423
00:25:02.750 --> 00:25:04.500
- You really saw him?
- Yes.

424
00:25:04.583 --> 00:25:06.224
No wonder he didn't visit me in my dream.

425
00:25:06.875 --> 00:25:08.083
Your father is unbelievable.

426
00:25:08.167 --> 00:25:10.125
Till yesterday.
he was excited about my wedding.

427
00:25:10.375 --> 00:25:13.250
He even suggested
I wear pink for the ceremony.

428
00:25:14.667 --> 00:25:19.333
Don't worry. I'll deal with him tonight
when he visits me in my dream again.

429
00:25:20.750 --> 00:25:22.333
Good morning. everyone.

430
00:25:22.917 --> 00:25:24.583
Does this sound funny to you. Mom?

431
00:25:25.667 --> 00:25:28.750
Kannu's engagement
was called off because of you.

432
00:25:30.375 --> 00:25:32.458
That's Tony's loss.

433
00:25:32.667 --> 00:25:34.750
Kannu won't run out of proposals.

434
00:25:35.042 --> 00:25:37.875
We'll find someone better.

435
00:25:41.083 --> 00:25:42.542
Sure.

436
00:25:42.625 --> 00:25:44.667
You can give this gift

437
00:25:44.750 --> 00:25:47.708
to that "better" guy.
What will I do with it?

438
00:25:47.792 --> 00:25:49.417
Never return a gift.

439
00:25:49.500 --> 00:25:51.792
Use it to buy a ticket back home.

440
00:25:51.875 --> 00:25:54.292
But the ticket is just 350 rupees.

441
00:25:54.375 --> 00:25:57.125
That's fine. He can use
the rest to buy snacks for the journey.

442
00:26:01.750 --> 00:26:02.750
Excuse me.

443
00:26:05.042 --> 00:26:06.125
Mother-in-law.

444
00:26:06.208 --> 00:26:08.083
is this the age to get married?

445
00:26:08.167 --> 00:26:09.042
Age is just a number.

446
00:26:09.125 --> 00:26:11.208
I look a couple of years
younger than you.

447
00:26:11.750 --> 00:26:12.792
Mom.

448
00:26:12.875 --> 00:26:15.792
don't you care what people will say?

449
00:26:15.875 --> 00:26:16.958
Son.

450
00:26:17.042 --> 00:26:18.583
as children. we don't know

451
00:26:18.667 --> 00:26:20.750
what people think of us.

452
00:26:21.125 --> 00:26:24.667
When we're young.
we don't care what they think.

453
00:26:25.667 --> 00:26:27.750
And in our old age. we realize

454
00:26:28.500 --> 00:26:30.750
they're not thinking about us at all.

455
00:26:33.250 --> 00:26:34.625
Vietnam?

456
00:26:35.417 --> 00:26:37.042
How did you end up there?

457
00:26:37.500 --> 00:26:41.292
My friends threw a party
for me for getting engaged.

458
00:26:41.750 --> 00:26:44.250
And I thought.
why waste the tickets?

459
00:26:44.583 --> 00:26:46.125
So I went along.

460
00:26:46.208 --> 00:26:47.208
Take care.

461
00:26:47.250 --> 00:26:49.042
<i>You too. Grandpa.</i>

462
00:26:49.125 --> 00:26:50.445
I'll be back in a couple of days.

463
00:26:50.917 --> 00:26:51.917
See you soon.

464
00:26:54.417 --> 00:26:55.417
Sorry. Tony.

465
00:26:56.417 --> 00:26:57.875
I don't know what's gotten into Mom.

466
00:26:58.333 --> 00:26:59.583
She isn't ready to listen.

467
00:26:59.667 --> 00:27:00.667
She'll listen.

468
00:27:01.083 --> 00:27:02.125
I'm sure.

469
00:27:02.208 --> 00:27:04.292
But first. we need to talk to your dad.

470
00:27:04.375 --> 00:27:05.708
How do we talk to Dad?

471
00:27:05.792 --> 00:27:06.875
He's in heaven...

472
00:27:06.958 --> 00:27:07.875
Not that one.

473
00:27:07.958 --> 00:27:10.125
The one who popped up
during the engagement...

474
00:27:10.208 --> 00:27:11.583
On the iPad.

475
00:27:12.167 --> 00:27:13.917
We need to find out who he is.

476
00:27:14.375 --> 00:27:16.042
Then we'll show him who we are.

477
00:27:16.667 --> 00:27:17.667
Who are we?

478
00:27:18.792 --> 00:27:19.958
You're an Ahuja

479
00:27:20.042 --> 00:27:22.125
not for long if he succeeds.

480
00:27:22.750 --> 00:27:23.875
Let's find him.

481
00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:26.268
Let's talk some sense into him.
No sugarcoating.

482
00:27:26.292 --> 00:27:28.542
No sugarcoating?
Should we stop his sugar supply?

483
00:27:29.333 --> 00:27:30.167
Is he for real?

484
00:27:30.250 --> 00:27:32.375
Will you just be quiet? I'm talking.

485
00:27:32.750 --> 00:27:35.030
A smart man is explaining something.
Try using your brain.

486
00:27:36.208 --> 00:27:37.542
What are you staring at?

487
00:27:38.333 --> 00:27:39.958
Over there. in the garden. Sister.

488
00:27:40.042 --> 00:27:41.101
They're plotting something.

489
00:27:41.125 --> 00:27:42.833
And 80 percent of crimes

490
00:27:42.917 --> 00:27:44.125
are committed by lovers.

491
00:27:44.208 --> 00:27:45.208
Shut up.

492
00:27:48.333 --> 00:27:50.792
Lead the way. Tony. We've got your back.

493
00:27:50.875 --> 00:27:52.458
You lead. I've got your back.

494
00:27:52.542 --> 00:27:53.417
Why me?

495
00:27:53.500 --> 00:27:54.708
Your mother.

496
00:27:54.958 --> 00:27:55.958
your daughter.

497
00:27:56.167 --> 00:27:57.708
your son-in-law. so you should lead.

498
00:27:58.292 --> 00:27:59.917
She's my mother too.

499
00:28:00.125 --> 00:28:02.042
You can lead as well.
Who's stopping you?

500
00:28:04.208 --> 00:28:06.958
Naag. you don't know
how to talk to people.

501
00:28:07.042 --> 00:28:08.792
So better stay quiet.

502
00:28:14.000 --> 00:28:15.476
What are you doing. Kannu?
Someone might see us.

503
00:28:15.500 --> 00:28:16.708
Hey. shut up.

504
00:28:18.542 --> 00:28:20.292
What were you planning
with Dad and Uncle?

505
00:28:20.667 --> 00:28:21.667
Planning?

506
00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:24.167
Nothing much.
I was thinking of heading back...

507
00:28:24.542 --> 00:28:29.125
But dad said... Your dad... He said
I should stay one more day. so I agreed.

508
00:28:29.208 --> 00:28:30.208
And what will you do?

509
00:28:31.583 --> 00:28:33.667
Spend time with your dad and uncle.

510
00:28:34.333 --> 00:28:35.333
No

511
00:28:35.542 --> 00:28:36.542
Not with them.

512
00:28:37.083 --> 00:28:38.917
Spend time with me.

513
00:28:39.375 --> 00:28:40.708
It's your last day here.

514
00:28:41.125 --> 00:28:42.667
I'll take you sightseeing in Shimla.

515
00:28:42.750 --> 00:28:44.000
Wow. why not?

516
00:28:44.500 --> 00:28:46.792
Our first outing together.

517
00:28:46.875 --> 00:28:47.708
And the last.

518
00:28:47.792 --> 00:28:49.083
- What?
- Nothing. Let's go.

519
00:28:55.042 --> 00:28:56.417
Mom...

520
00:28:57.750 --> 00:28:58.958
By the way.

521
00:28:59.667 --> 00:29:01.917
who are you marrying?

522
00:29:04.500 --> 00:29:06.667
You'll find out soon enough.

523
00:29:07.583 --> 00:29:08.583
For now.

524
00:29:08.667 --> 00:29:10.458
you've come to Shimla after so long.

525
00:29:10.542 --> 00:29:12.833
go enjoy. do some sightseeing.

526
00:29:25.292 --> 00:29:28.958
<i>♪ Hear me out. I place my heart ♪</i>

527
00:29:30.042 --> 00:29:33.250
<i>♪ At your service. my love ♪</i>

528
00:29:34.042 --> 00:29:38.250
<i>♪ It won't stop pleading. my love ♪</i>

529
00:29:38.750 --> 00:29:42.708
<i>♪ It longs to be yours forever ♪</i>

530
00:29:42.792 --> 00:29:47.333
<i>♪ Down the lanes of love it wanders ♪</i>

531
00:29:47.417 --> 00:29:50.667
<i>♪ With no thought of turning back ♪</i>

532
00:29:51.583 --> 00:29:55.833
